Each Group is modular with image input and output for clear understanding of what each one does.

I renamed the vae from the original "ae.safetensors" to make it obviously for flux. I recommend you do that.

Flux doesn't use the negative prompt but the other two do, so it's included. 

I like the low step generation in flux to get a rough composition. 1-3 steps usually, depending on the subject matter. I think flux way over-bakes the content at 20 steps, pulling them away from compositions that I preferred at those lower steps. 1 step will give rougher and more distressed results, and up to 4 steps will have better text generation and less noise.

SD3 does a great job of adding detail and refining the rough composition in the Flux generation.

SDXL-turbo is fast enough for a quick ULTIMATE upscale. Lightning might be your flavor there, or even a SDXL community model. I like RealVis XL V3 Turbo.

* Feel free to bypass the LoRAs and swap to your favorite upscalers.
